                        <customfieldname>Steps to Reproduce</customfieldname>
                        <customfieldvalues>
                            <customfieldvalue>&lt;p&gt;1. On a clean installation of Fuse 6.1, add the ServiceMix BCEL JAR to the lib/endorsed directory (&lt;a href=&quot;http://search.maven.org/remotecontent?filepath=org/apache/servicemix/bundles/org.apache.servicemix.bundles.bcel/5.2_4/org.apache.servicemix.bundles.bcel-5.2_4.jar&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://search.maven.org/remotecontent?filepath=org/apache/servicemix/bundles/org.apache.servicemix.bundles.bcel/5.2_4/org.apache.servicemix.bundles.bcel-5.2_4.jar&lt;/a&gt;) This is needed by Xalan&lt;br/&gt;
2. Unpack the attached reproducer (this is an Eclipse project)&lt;br/&gt;
3. Deploy reproducer jar on Fuse using osgi:install&lt;br/&gt;
4. Note the error message in the log:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ERROR:  &apos;Cannot find class &apos;something.JavaFunction&apos;.&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
FATAL ERROR:  &apos;Could not compile stylesheet&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
